HIST 4B
Click box to close.      
Full Title: Western Civilization
Description: 1050 to 1715. History 4A-B-C is a general survey course, designed to acquaint the student with major developments that have influenced the course of western civilization since the earliest times. These developmentsare as likely to be in religion, the arts, and sciences as in the more traditional policical field. Weekly discussion sections are an important feature of this course, enabling the student to develop and expand upon material presented during the lecture hour.
PreRequisite:
College: L&S
Units: 4.0
Grading: Optional
Textbook Information: http://www.ucsbstuff.com/SelectTermDept.aspx
